  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "QUANTITY SURVEYOR",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Manage the full spectrum of quantity surveying duties including procurement, budgeting, cost estimation, contract administration, and measurement of quantities.</li><li>Evaluate and process variation orders and support cost control efforts throughout project life cycles.</li><li>Source and assess new subcontractors and suppliers to ensure competitive pricing and quality standards.</li><li>Prepare and issue Request for Quotation (RFQ) and tender documents in coordination with relevant departments.</li><li>Review and compare subcontractor/supplier quotations, conduct evaluations, and provide recommendations.</li><li>Participate in procurement meetings and support the preparation of price data and procurement reports.</li><li>Provide tendering support, especially in pricing exercises and Value Engineering/Cost Down (VECD) proposals.</li><li>Collaborate with site teams to support contract administration, including main contracts, subcontract management, interim payments, and final accounts.</li><li>Assist the QS Manager in managing all contractual and financial aspects of construction projects to ensure compliance and profitability.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Relevant working experience in quantity surveying, with site-based experience preferred.</li><li>Strong analytical skills and attention to detail, with a good understanding of construction processes and contract law.</li><li>Excellent interpersonal, communication, and negotiation skills to manage internal and external stakeholders effectively.</li><li>Proactive, resourceful, and able to work both independently and in a team environment</li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 5,
